
[1]basanite

   BAS'ANITE, n. [Gr. the trier. Plin.Lib.36. Ca.22. See Basalt.]

   Lydian stone, or black jasper; a variety of siliceous or flinty slate.
   Its color is a grayish or bluish black, interspersed with veins of
   quartz. It is employed to test the purity of gold.
